sql_command:
SELECT 
    AVG(CASE WHEN card_type = 'Credit' THEN balance ELSE NULL END) AS avg_credit_balance,
    AVG(CASE WHEN card_type = 'Debit' THEN balance ELSE NULL END) AS avg_debit_balance
FROM (
  SELECT 
      customer_id, 
      CASE 
          WHEN card_number LIKE '%Visa%' THEN 'Credit'
          WHEN card_number LIKE '%Mastercard%' THEN 'Credit'
          WHEN card_number LIKE '%Amex%' THEN 'Credit'
          ELSE 'Debit'
      END AS card_type,
      balance
  FROM banking_new."Cards"
) AS subquery
GROUP BY customer_id;

sql_command:
SELECT 
    AVG(A.account_balance) AS avg_balance
FROM 
    banking_new."Accounts" A
JOIN 
    banking_new."Transactions" T ON A.account_id = T.account_id
WHERE 
    T.transaction_date >= NOW() - INTERVAL '90 days'
GROUP BY 
    A.account_number;

What is the shortest payment term for a loan with an interest rate above 6%?
sql_command:
SELECT 
    L.loan_identifier,
    L.payment_term
FROM 
    banking_new."Loans" L
JOIN 
    banking_new."LoanTypes" LT ON L.loan_type_id = LT.loan_type_id
WHERE 
    L.interest_rate > 6 AND 
    (SELECT COUNT(*) FROM banking_new."Loans" WHERE loan_type_id = L.loan_type_id AND payment_term = L.payment_term) = (
        SELECT COUNT(*) FROM banking_new."LoanTypes" WHERE loan_type_id = LT.loan_type_id
    )
ORDER BY 
    L.payment_term;

What is the largest withdrawal (most negative transaction) recorded?
sql_command:
SELECT 
    t.transaction_amount AS "Largest Withdrawal"
FROM 
    banking_new."Transactions" t
JOIN 
    banking_new."Customers" c ON t.account_id = c.customer_id
WHERE 
    t.transaction_amount < 0
ORDER BY 
    t.transaction_amount DESC
LIMIT 1;
